{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"07382fd6-c2c9-492f-8ab0-5bf85246e8ac","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues in this project:\n\n## 1. Expensive Recursive Glob (Line 9, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\n`**\\*.*` forces MSBuild to walk the entire directory tree during evaluation. This is one of the most expensive evaluation-time operations, especially as the project grows.\n\n## 2. File I/O via Property Function (Line 13, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nReading file contents during evaluation blocks the evaluation pipeline with synchronous I/O. This runs on every evaluation (IDE load, design-time build, etc.).\n\n## 3. Deeply Chained Imports (3 levels)\n```\nEvalHeavy.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach import requires file resolution, parsing, and merging. Three levels of chaining adds latency that compounds in solutions with many projects.\n\n---\n\n**Recommendations:**\n- Replace the recursive glob with explicit file lists or narrower patterns.\n- Move file reading to a target (executes at build-time, not evaluation-time).\n- Flatten the import chain — merge the `.props` files or reduce nesting.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f3a5fde2-1a98-4baf-a04a-c68df20f9c09","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a complete picture of the project. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.\n\nIssues I can see:\n\n1. **Deeply chained imports** (level1.props → level2.props → level3.props): This creates a 3-level deep import chain that MSBuild must resolve during evaluation. Each import requires file I/O and parsing.\n\n2. **Recursive glob pattern** (`**\\*.*`): The `AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\"` glob is extremely expensive during evaluation because it walks the entire directory tree. This is one of the most common causes of slow evaluation.\n\n3. **Property function that reads files at evaluation time**: `$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))` performs file I/O during evaluation, which is expensive and blocks the evaluation pipeline.\n\n\nThese three bottlenecks are the primary culprits slowing down your build evaluation—the nested imports force repeated file resolution, the recursive glob pattern triggers expensive directory traversal, and the inline file read operation blocks the entire evaluation process.","outputTokens":548,"requestId":"0416:71A4F:BF6419:DC85E0:69F2AEFB"},"id":"c86e7608-b772-4581-a2f5-961909b66c0d","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:23:18.496Z","parentId":"f1cf5fdf-4f3f-420b-bfc9-fc4eaaaf744c"}
